pider that we had killed, but he gave the loots to me after i said something) and he asks me to rez his ledge group that wiped due to an overpull.  I tell him I would provided he can drag the corpses to the zone (clerics dont get invisibility) which he agrees to.  So I rez the corpses and he invites me to their group which consists of a rogue I don't care for, a monk I don't know that well, and myself.  I decide to stay because what the heck it's christmas, I can look beyond my differences for a shot at a ledge group!  So we make our way up to the ledge and make it safely.  First pull, here comes 7 spiders...  uhhh...  druid says <br>
evac?<br>
rogue dies<br>
evac?<br>
monk dies<br>
evac?<br>
we all die.<br>
uhhhhhhh   if you think we should evac chances are you ought to have evac'd.  <br>
but I didnt say anything I just told the group I would be looking for a sow for the corpse run (was bound in Plain of Knowledge)  Then the rogue tells the group that he has to leave.  Ole' Garfo happens to be there and throws a sow my way (Thank Brell for Pie Filled Halflings!)  I then notice that the monk has gone link dead, and that the druid has camped without saying a word to anyone.<br>
/cry<br>
So I run back through Great Divide with my trusty Halo of Light, 4 Breads, 4 waters and my hammer of requital (I like to cast these things so i dont feel totally nekkid but in reality (wait reality oh ya this is just a game, i keep forgetting) they help very little)).<br>
It is at this point I get a apologetic tell from the monk explaining that he was on his way back to velks to help out with the corpse retrieval.  I am thinking great this might just work out ok, I have seen monks get corpses before so we should be golden.  But I buffed him with Heroism just in case.  He died anyway.  Score spiders 2, Monk 0.  He comes back to velks and makes another go.  This time I give him resist poison.  Score another one for the spiders.  A third attempt, and another point to the spiders later, I see a friendly rogue in the zone.  If you ever see a Halfling named Xeter, give her a huge hug and a kiss.  She is the best!  She tells me to tell the monk to stop and consent her.  By this time the monk has died yet again and now has a total of 5 corpses scattered around the ledge.  Xeter, bless her, drags all the monks corpses plus my own in one shot!  woot i got my stuff back!  So I start looting my gear so that I can rez the monk a bit easier, leaving my bags on my corpse.  So I rez the monk 2 or 3 times and get distracted because another cleric comes in and starts rezzing him before the rez effects wear off.  Now I could be wrong, but it is my understanding that If a person has more then one corpse, and still has rez effects on, that they will not get xp back on the next rez.  So I tell the cleric to hold off, and the monk not to accept those rezzs.  but it's too late, and now the monk has no more corpses for me to rez.<br>
Oh well, better loot the rest of my stuff.<br>
/loot<br>
I stand up, look at my xp bar, look on the ground, and realize that uhh...<br>
I forgot to rez myself!!1!<br>
*insert sounds of sobbing here*<br>
I went from being 19% into level 52, to 9% in the blink of an eye.<br>
Oh i got it all back, but it took me 2 hours<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
This is as far as I can say, the st00pidist thing I ever did done.<br>
<br>
/em bonks himself<br>
