<br>
you are wrong. the status of the character _being_ rezzed doesn't matter a single whit. When you rez a corpse, as soon as they click 'yes', the Mystical Invisible Exp Item is removed from that corpse. Now, until the rez timer goes away, you can rez, staple, mutilate, crush, fold, bend, taunt, or drag that corpse however you want, and it doesn't matter. Once it's been rezzed once, it's useless.<br>
<br>
As for chain-rezzing, I assure you, after chewing through a 13-corpse pile of my own (thank god for epic), it does not matter if you have rez FX on or not. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Hitumfast, level 4x HFL/WAR<br>
